<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en"
      xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
      xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
      xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
      lang="en"
      metal:use-macro="context/main_template/macros/master"
      i18n:domain="plone">
<body>
<metal:main metal:fill-slot="content">
  <div id="content"
          class="documentEditable">
                <h1><span i18n:translate="heading_member_profile">Member Profile</span>
                <span class="rhaptossmall">(view profile)</span>
                </h1>

            <h5 class="hiddenStructure">Views</h5>

            <ul class="contentViews">
              <li class="">
                <a href=""
                   tal:attributes="href string:${portal_url}/personalize_form"
                   i18n:translate="label_edit">Personal Information</a>
              </li>
              <li>
                <a href=""
                   tal:attributes="href string: ${portal_url}/Members/${member}/@@my_links"
                   i18n:translate="label_view">My Links</a>
              </li>
              <li class="selected">
                <a href=""
                   tal:attributes="href string: ${portal_url}/Members/${member}/@@my_features"
                   i18n:translate="label_view">Featured Content</a>
              </li>
            </ul>

Feature up to two of the collections or modules you have authored in a specially highlighted area above the full content listing on your author profile.


<div class="context"><a href=""
                   tal:attributes="href string: ${portal_url}/Members/${member}/createObject?type_name=FeaturedContent"
>+ Add a featured collection or module</a></div>

  </div>


</metal:main>
</body>
</html>
